And a lot of what we call investment

36:57.080 --> 37:00.280
is about the financialization of the economy.

37:00.280 --> 37:03.040
But as our economy has become more financialized,

37:03.040 --> 37:05.960
then innovation has gone down, not up.

37:05.960 --> 37:09.680
And what we've seen then is a capture of wealth by capital

37:09.680 --> 37:13.280
that the extensive labor or workers use that drum,

37:13.280 --> 37:14.880
because capital isn't an entity,

37:14.880 --> 37:17.480
capital is a factor of production.

37:17.480 --> 37:19.840
But what we have seen is an economy

37:19.840 --> 37:22.320
because of the financialization and the emphasis

37:22.320 --> 37:24.240
on rent seeking and rent capture.

37:24.240 --> 37:26.600
We have an economy that is less fair,

