01:20:50.120 --> 01:20:54.040
sector, and that's about twice as much as other industrialized

01:20:54.040 --> 01:20:57.080
countries, and we have worse life expectancy.

01:20:57.080 --> 01:20:59.760
And that's an example where we're spending more than we should

01:20:59.760 --> 01:21:02.560
be to get an outcome that we don't like very much.

01:21:02.560 --> 01:21:05.920
And that's the product of a whole bunch with misaligned incentives

01:21:05.920 --> 01:21:10.000
that were structured to facilitate red capture.

01:21:10.000 --> 01:21:13.720
Glad I put this part on getting red capture and monopoly

01:21:13.720 --> 01:21:17.280
power out of the economy.

01:21:17.280 --> 01:21:18.760
I think that's it.

01:21:18.760 --> 01:21:22.520
